'''Leonardo "Léo" Pereira''' ({{IPA|pt|ˈlɛ.u peˈɾejɾɐ}}; born 31 January 1996) is a Brazilian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

==Club career==
===Atlético Paranaense===
Born in [[Curitiba]], [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]], Léo Pereira finished his formation with [[Clube Atlético Paranaense|Atlético Paranaense]]. He made his [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Série A]] debut on 3 May 2014, replacing [[Marcos Guilherme]] in a 2–3 home loss against [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/jogo/brasileirao2014/03-05-2014/atletico-pr-cruzeiro.html|title=Cruzeiro reage duas vezes e consegue virada para cima do Furacão|trans-title=Cruzeiro reacts twice and completes comeback over ''Furacão''|publisher=Globo Esporte|language=pt|date=3 May 2014|accessdate=15 April 2015}}</ref> He went on to make a further thirteen league appearances in 2014.

====Loans to Guaratinguetá and Náutico====
Pereira joined [[Guaratinguetá Futebol|Guaratinguetá]] of [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série C|Série C]] on loan in August 2015 where he made eight appearances before returning to Atlético in October 2015.<ref name="Léo Pereira on Soccerway">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/leonardo-pereira/288077/|title=Léo Pereira on Soccerway|publisher=Soccerway|date=21 October 2015|accessdate=21 October 2015}}</ref> On 23 May 2016, he moved to [[Clube Náutico Capibaribe|Náutico]] also in a temporary deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mg.superesportes.com.br/app/noticias/ultimas-noticias/1,1208,18,98/2016/05/23/noticia_nautico,42583/novamente-apostando-em-jovens-nautico-contrata-zagueiro-leo-pereira-de-20-anos.shtml|title=Novamente apostando em jovens, Náutico contrata zagueiro Léo Pereira, de 20 anos|trans-title=Again betting on youngsters, Náutico sign centre-back Léo Pereira, aged 20|publisher=Super Esportes|language=pt-BR|date=23 May 2016|accessdate=19 May 2026}}</ref>

====Loan to Orlando City====
On 14 March 2017, Pereira joined [[Orlando City B]], the [[United Soccer League|USL]] affiliate of [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]], on a season long loan. He was the first player to move between the two clubs since they became official partners the previous November.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/post/2017/03/14/ocb-acquires-clube-atl-tico-paranaense-defender-l-o-pereira-loan|title=OCB Acquires Clube Atlético Paranaense Defender Léo Pereira on Loan|publisher=Orlando City|date=14 March 2017|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> After beginning the season with Orlando City B, he was called up to the first team in mid-April and made his [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] debut against San Jose Earthquakes on 17 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/post/2017/05/17/starting-xi-vs-san-jose-mid-week-shake|title=Starting XI vs. San Jose|publisher=Orlando City|date=17 May 2017|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref>

====Breakthrough====
Back to Atlético for the 2018 season, Pereira was initially a backup under head coach [[Fernando Diniz]], before becoming a starter under [[Tiago Nunes]] and finishing the year with six goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tribunapr.com.br/esportes/athletico/leo-pereira-foi-um-dos-destaques-do-athletico-em-2018/|title=Conheça a trajetória de Léo Pereira, um dos destaques do Athletico em 2018|trans-title=Know the trajectory of Léo Pereira, one of Athletico's spotlights in 2018|publisher=Tribuna PR|language=pt-BR|date=28 December 2018|accessdate=19 May 2026}}</ref>

===Flamengo===
On 28 January 2020, [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] signed Pereira from Athletico Paranaense in a [[Euro|€]]6.1m transfer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/pr/futebol/noticia/flamengo-leo-pereira-contratacao-pablo-mari-arsenal-athletico.ghtml |title=Pablo Marí viaja para fechar com o Arsenal, e Flamengo acerta contratação de Léo Pereira, do Athletico |website=ge.globo|language=pt-br |date=28 January 2020 |access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref> On 27 January 2023, established as a first-choice, he extended his contract with the club until 31 December 2027.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/2023/01/27/flamengo-renova-contrato-de-leo-pereira-ate-o-fim-de-2027.ghtml |title=Flamengo renova contrato de Léo Pereira até o fim de 2027 |website=ge.globo |language=pt-BR |date=27 January 2023|access-date=27 January 2023}}</ref>

In an impressive 2025 campaign, Pereira emerged as one of the most utilized players in the squad, appearing in 63 matches with 62 starts. He scored six goals and providing one assist during the year, with 22 key passes and a 92% pass completion rate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lance.com.br/flamengo/compare-numeros-de-vitao-com-principais-zagueiros-do-flamengo.html|title=Compare números de Vitão com principais zagueiros do Flamengo|trans-title=|publisher=Lance|date=|access-date=December 30, 2025|language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Pereira has made twelve appearances across two age levels for the Brazil national team. He received his first call up to the [[Brazil national under-17 football team|U17s]] when he was selected for the [[2013 South American Under-17 Football Championship]] in April. He made two appearances in Argentina against [[Peru national under-17 football team|Peru]] and [[Venezuela national under-17 football team|Venezuela]]. His final U17 caps came in October and November when he was called up for the [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in the United Arab Emirates. The first coming in the Group Stage against [[Honduras national under-17 football team|Honduras]] and the second in a quarter-final penalty shoot-out defeat to [[Mexico national under-17 football team|Mexico]] in which Pereira scored a spot-kick in the shoot-out.<ref name="Léo Pereira on Soccerway"/>

Two years later Pereira appeared in five of Brazil's [[2015 South American Youth Football Championship]] matches, with two caps coming against [[Colombia national under-20 football team|Colombia]] and the other three coming against [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay]], [[Paraguay men's national under-20 football team|Paraguay]] and [[Peru national under-20 football team|Peru]] who he also scored against. Later that year he played in three of Brazil's [[2015 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] matches. The first two came in the Group Stage against [[Hungary national under-19 football team|Hungary]] and [[North Korea national under-20 football team|North Korea]], he scored a goal against the latter, and his last U20 World Cup cap was versus [[Senegal national under-20 football team|Senegal]] in a 5–0 semi-final win. Brazil subsequently made it to the final which they lost to [[Serbia national under-20 football team|Serbia]], Pereira was an unused substitute.<ref name="Léo Pereira on Soccerway"/>

===Senior===
After being included several times on the pre-lists for the national team, Pereira finally was called by [[Carlo Ancelotti]] for the main Brazil squad on 16 March 2026, for friendlies against [[France national football team|France]] and [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], on the final months of preparation building up the squad prior to the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 March 2026 |title=Brazil: Brentford's Igor Thiago and Bournemouth's Rayan receive first call-ups |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c8eg0y22w2ro |access-date=17 March 2026 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He made his full international debut ten days later, starting in a 2–1 loss against the former.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/selecao-brasileira/artigo/_/id/16500150/leo-pereira-compara-estreia-selecao-jogos-flamengo-responde-como-encarar-mbappe|title=Léo Pereira compara estreia pela seleção aos jogos do Flamengo e responde como foi encarar Mbappé|trans-title=Léo Pereira compares debut in the national team to Flamengo matches and answers how it was to face Mbappé|publisher=[[ESPN Brasil]]|language=pt-BR|date=28 March 2026|accessdate=19 May 2026}}</ref>

On 18 May 2026, Pereira was included in Ancelotti's 26-man squad for the World Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/2026/05/19/leo-pereira-do-flamengo-se-joga-na-piscina-ao-saber-de-convocacao-para-a-copa-do-mundo-veja.ghtml|title=Léo Pereira, do Flamengo, se joga na piscina ao saber de convocação para a Copa do Mundo; veja|trans-title=Léo Pereira, from Flamengo, throws himself in the pool after knowing he was called up to the World Cup; check it out|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|ge]]|language=pt-BR|date=19 May 2026|accessdate=19 May 2026}}</ref>

